cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.RO 

This paper is about using Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) techniques to efficiently find counterexamples that falsify the given properties of a Cyber-Physical System (CPS). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems such as CPS. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically DRL, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexities involved in software and physical systems, indicating that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper mentions the application of CPS in autonomous automobiles, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
